  "texts": [
    "2021b) ~ /mindspore/graphlearning -MindSpore-based graph learning library DIG (Liu et al. 2021b) ~ /divelab/DIG -unified testing platform Graphvite (Zhu et al.",
    "2019) ~ /deepgraphlearning/graphvite -high-speed and large-scale embedding learning 1 3",
    "GraphScope (Fan et al. 2021) is a one-stop graph computing platform developed and open-sourced by the Intelligent Computing Lab of Alibaba's DAMO Academy, supporting the storage, querying, and analysis of large-scale graph data.",
    "GeaFlow (Pan et al. 2023) is a high-performance graph database open-sourced by the Ant Group, which provides storage, querying, and computation of graph data and graph algorithms.",
    "CuGraph (Fender et al. 2022) is an acceleration framework on NVIDIA GPUs for the efficient computation of graph algorithms, especially suitable for processing and analyzing large-scale graph data."
